\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 In common English parlance, the term property refers to things or objects such as a house, a land, a car, a table\'85
etc. It also refers to the right of ownership of person. Hence, you commonly hear a person claiming that a certain thing or object is his property, that some body took his property\'85
etc. However, the term, in its legal usage, refers to the rights a person may have in relation to things or objects that have economic value. The things or objects in relation to which property rights ar
e exercised are called d objects of property. Hence, property refers to rights such as ownership, possession, usufruct, use, and rights of servitude, recovery, preemption and promise of sale.
\par The branch of law that specifies the objects or things in relati
on to which property rights may be exercised and their classification, the types of rights which are considered as property, how property rights are acquired, transferred, extinguished, the specific rights and obligations of the property right holder, the
 obligations of other persons to wards the holder is known as property law. In general, property law may be defined as a branch of private law regulating relations between persons with respect to things or objects.
\par Book III Title IV, Arts 1126-1674 of the Civil Code of Ethiopia, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3624146\charrsid11362428 which }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 is the main body of the property law of the country}{
