\b\highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327 by the law of obligations}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 , i.e., by the law of contracts when they arise out of contractual relations and by the l
aw of torts when they arise out of extra-contractual relations. These categories of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327 patrimonial rights}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid13840327\charrsid13840327 
, arising out of contractual or extra-contractual relationsi,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327  are also referred to as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327 
rights in-personam / personal rights/}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327  because they can be exercised against a specific person or persons.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
 On the other hand, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327 patrimonial rights over things/ property rights/ are governed by the law of property and they are also called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\ul\highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327 rights in-rem/ real rights}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13840327 / since they can be exercised against any person who may interfere with the right-holder\rquote 
