\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Like all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5327653\charrsid11362428 other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 law}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5327653\charrsid11362428 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 , property law seeks to articulate the principles, policies, and rules by which disputes are to be resolved and by which transa
ctions may be structured so that disputes may be avoided. What distinguishes property law from other kinds of law }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13644873 
is that the principles, policies, and rules of property law deal with the relationships between and among members of a society with respect to things. The things may be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13644873  tangible}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13644873 , such as land, a factory, or a diamond ring or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13644873 intangible}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\highlight7\insrsid2119398\charrsid13644873 , such as stocks and bonds or a bank account.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
