\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \highlight3\insrsid2119398\charrsid9844956 Property law, then, deals with the allocation, use, and transfer of wealth and objects of wealth.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
 As such, it reflects the economy of the society in which it is found. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid2119398\charrsid9844956 In this regard Art 89/1/ of the FDRE Constitution imposes, on the government, to formulate 
and implement policies /and laws/ that ensure equal and fair allocation of the country\rquote s intellectual and material resources}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 .
