The person must give its freedom an external sphere in order to live as an idea. This external sphere, capable of embodying the person\rquote s freedom, consists}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16522109  of the rest of the word, every}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 thing that is dist
inct from the person. From the need to embody the person's free will from the abstract realm to the actual, Hegel concludes that the person becomes a real self only by engaging in a property relationship with something external. Such a relationship is the
 goal of the person. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428  
