\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
All property relations in the past have continually been subject to historical change consequent upon the change in historical conditions. The French Revolution, for example, abolished feudal proper
ty in favour of bourgeois property. The distinguishing feature of Communism is not the abolition of property generally, but the abolition of bourgeois property. But modern bourgeois private property is the final and most complete expression of the system 
of producing and appropriating products that is based on class antagonisms, on the exploitation of the many by the few.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid2119398 
