However, the natural proposition that ownership of the land implies the title to what ever is above it cannot be reversed to conclude that the ownership of works on it implies ownership/holding of the land. Nor does the ownership of the subsoil, for ex
ample, a cave or a subterranean quarry, carry a legal presumption that the owner owns/holds also the surface. See Art 1209, 1210 and 1214 of the Civil Code.
