\jclisttab\tx780\tx1260\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls49\adjustright\rin0\lin780\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
Commingling /fusion/ - occurs when two dry or liquid things /matters belonging to different owners are commingled or fused so that they cannot be
 separated with out difficulty. In such cases, the persons, in proportion to value of the material each owned, shall jointly own the new to thing so formed.  For instance, where ink belonging to two different persons are mixed to form an ink with a differ
ent color, the new thing/ink/ shall be jointly owned by the persons in proportion to value of the ink each used to own. See Art 1183(2).   
