\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Read the obligations of the usufructuary and identify the major rights of the bare owner.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\qj \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\sl360\slmult1\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\fs24\insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc175128730}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc204104785}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc229915068}
5.5 EXTINCTION OF USUFRUCT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\fs24\insrsid2119398 {\*\bkmkend _Toc175128730}{\*\bkmkend _Toc204104785}{\*\bkmkend _Toc229915068}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid91394 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid91394\charrsid91394 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
The right of usufruct shall be extinguished for either of the following reasons;  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid91394\charrsid11362428 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1.\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-360\li780\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar
\jclisttab\tx780\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls22\adjustright\rin0\lin780\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
Death of the usufructuary- a right of usufruct is some times called a personal servitude because it depends on the life of the usufructuary. In other words, the right of usufruct shall terminate up on the death of the usufructuary.  See Art 1322(1) 

\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2.\tab}
Lapse of the period for which it is created. For example, a usufruct created for a period of five years shall terminate at the end of the five years. Art 1322(1)
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3.\tab}Extinctive prescription \endash 
 lack of exercise of any of the usufruct rights or complete absence enjoyment, use possession by the usufructuary or by his agent in relation to chattels/ ordinary corporeal movable things/ shall result in the termination o
f usufruct. See Art 1310 cum 1192 of the Civil Code.    
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 4.\tab}
The loss or destruction of the thing; Similar to the case of loss of ownership right, usufruct shall also be extinguished as a result of the loss or destruction of the object of property. See Arts 1319, 1310 cum 1188 of the Civil Code.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 5.\tab}
Consolidation or merger of the position of the bare owner and the usufructuary in one person shall also result in the extinction of usufruct right. This happens when the usufructuary acquires bare ownership (by co
ntract or succession) or when the bare owner acquires the usufruct by contract. See Arts 1676/1/ cum 1842 of the Civil Code.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 6.\tab}Forfeiture or waiver of right by the usufructuary; A right of usufruct of chattels shall be extinguished where the usufructuary 
expresses, clearly and unequivocally, his intention to waive his rights as a usufructuary. See Arts 1310 cum1191 of the Civil Code. Refer also to Art 1676/1/ cum 1825 of the Civil Code. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li420\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin420\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
 Should this provision apply to the extinction of usufruct over immovable things and special movable things? Note that the provisions of Art 1191 apply to chattels only.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 7.\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-360\li780\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar
\jclisttab\tx780\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls22\adjustright\rin0\lin780\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Acquisitive prescription in favor of a third party; As we have seen in relation to owne
rship right, the right of usufruct shall be extinguished as a result of acquisition of usufruct right on the thing in favor of another person. See Art 1310 cum 1168 of the Civil Code.
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\qc \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\sl360\slmult1\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid91394 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\insrsid2119398\charrsid91394 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc175128731}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc204104786}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc229915069}5.6 RIGHT OF USE AND HABITATION
{\*\bkmkend _Toc175128731}{\*\bkmkend _Toc204104786}{\*\bkmkend _Toc229915069}
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s2\qj \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\sl360\slmult1\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\fs24\insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
{\*\bkmkstart _Toc175128732}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc204104787}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc229915070}5.6.1 RIGHT OF USE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\fs24\insrsid2119398 {\*\bkmkend _Toc175128732}{\*\bkmkend _Toc204104787}{\*\bkmkend _Toc229915070}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid91394 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid91394\charrsid91394 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
Right of use is a temporary real right (for agreed period of time or for life the beneficiary) which entitles the beneficiary, called the user, to use a thing of another person and to receive its fruits such as profits or rents\'85
 but only with in the limits of his own and his family's needs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Right of use may be created by an agreement, with or without consideration, or by will.
\par Under French Law, use right over land may be acquired, in the same manner as usufruct, by acquisitive prescription of 10 to 20 years, or 30 years, on condition that the user was himself in possession of the land.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 The right of use is not recognized under the Ethiopian Civil Code; hence we shall briefly see the rights and obligations of the user under the French Civil Code.
\par The rights and obligations of the user are governed by the instrument that created the use right, but in the absence of such provisions in the instrument the user will have the following rights and obligations. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1)\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-360\li720\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar
\jclisttab\tx720\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls50\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
The user has the right to the profits or fruits of the thing proportional to his and his family's needs. He can claim the various fruits or produce only in an amount in wh
ich each kind of produce will be consumed by him and his family, i.e., spouse, children and servants. However, collateral family members and ascendants are not included. 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2)\tab} The user has the same duties as a usufructuary. Please, read the discussion regarding the duties of the usufructuary.  
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3)\tab}
The user cannot transfer, assign or lease his right, or substitute a third party, hence, the right of use may not be seized by the creditors of the user, even if it was constituted for consideration. But he can sel
l a portion of the fruits, which he acquired in ownership by taking them directly or having them delivered. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li720\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid91394 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid91394\charrsid11362428 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
The right of use is extinguished in the same manner as the right of usufruct is extinguished.
\par  
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\qj \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\sl360\slmult1\keepn\widctlpar\tx6450\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\fs24\insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 {\*\bkmkstart _Toc175128734}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc204104789}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc229915071}
5.6.2 RIGHT OF HABITATION /OCCUPATION OF PREMISES{\*\bkmkend _Toc175128734}{\*\bkmkend _Toc204104789}/}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai0\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \i0\f0\fs24\insrsid2119398 {\*\bkmkend _Toc229915071}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid91394 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid91394\charrsid91394 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
This right is merely a particular type of right of use, i.e., a right of use exercised over residential houses or premises. Hence, the rules discussed in relation to
 usufruct and use rights are applicable to the right of habitation or right of occupation of premises. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Normally, the physical scope of the right of habitation is determined by the instrument creating it. Unless there are restrictions or reservations in t
he instrument, the right of habitation includes the whole house, which is its object and all its accessories. However, the beneficiary must not exercise his right beyond the needs of his and his family's residence. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Art 1353 of the Civil Code defines the 
right of habitation or right of occupation of premises as a right to live in a house or part of a house belonging to another person. The beneficiary of the right of habitation has the right to live in the house with his/her spouse, direct ascendants, desc
endants and servants. See Art 1354 of the Civil Code.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid91394\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
The beneficiary of right of habitation whose right is limited to part of a house also has the right to use parts of the building/house and the compound that are intended for the common use of all occupiers of the building. See Art 1355 of the Civil Code.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 
The beneficiary of the right of habitation has an obligation to cover costs required for regular repairs and maintenance of the house in which he lives. However, where his right is limited to part of th
e building and the owner occupies the other part of the building such expenses are to be covered by the owner of the house. See Art 1356 of the Civil Code.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2052544\charrsid11362428 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2119398\charrsid11362428 Similar to the rights of usufruct and use, a right of habitation is personal to the beneficiary and hence cannot be transferred and may not pass to his heirs. See Art 1357 of the Civil Code. 

\par Generally, in addition to these rules, the rules governing usufruct shall also apply to the right of habitation or occupation of premises. Refer to Art 1358 of the Civil Code. 
\par 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\qj \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\sl360\slmult1\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11362428 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
